in time.

51
00:01:54,980 --> 00:01:56,829
So when people started getting arrested

52
00:01:56,829 --> 00:01:58,560
for using coal,

53
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:00,450
they didn’t have any alternative.

54
00:02:00,660 --> 00:02:03,340
Well, except to freeze, I guess.

55
00:02:03,340 --> 00:02:06,340
And in places where natural gas was available,

56
00:02:06,340 --> 00:02:09,569
massive shortages made prices skyrocket.

57
00:02:09,569 --> 00:02:10,809
According to Tencent,

58
00:02:10,809 --> 00:02:14,379
“One senior couple secretly burned coal
for heat,

59
00:02:14,379 --> 00:02:16,799
and died of carbon monoxide (CO) poisoning

60
00:02:16,799 --> 00:02:19,069
due to poor ventilation.

61
00:02:19,069 --> 00:02:20,340
Even in areas where natural gas

62
00:02:20,340 --> 00:02:22,340
and electricity are available,

63
00:02:22,340 --> 00:02:23,739
low-income families complain

64
00:02:23,739 --> 00:02:26,129
that they are too expensive.”

65
00:02:26,129 --> 00:02:27,689
Stories of people burning sticks

66
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:30,010
and corncobs to keep warm

67
00:02:30,010 --> 00:02:32,719
have been going viral on China’s internet.

68
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:34,680
So have photos of children having class

69
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:36,560
outside in their coats—

70
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,580
because at least you can’t be arrested

71
00:02:38,580 --> 00:02:41,040
for letting the sun keep you warm.

72
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:42,669
For now.

73
00:02:42,669 --> 00:02:44,129
As Bloomberg put it,

74
00:02:44,129 --> 00:02:46,840
all this became “another example of how

75
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:49,519
China’s bureaucracy can sometimes subordinate

76
00:02:49,519 --> 00:02:53,340
common sense to centrally mandated goals.”

77
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:56,169
Mmm, the success of central planning.

78
00:02:56,169 --> 00:02:58,480
Here’s how it works in China:

79
00:02:58,480 --> 00:02:59,680
the central government issues

80
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,909
a high-level policy directive,

81
00:03:01,909 --> 00:03:04,639
like reducing the number of coal-burning households

82
00:03:04,639 --> 00:03:07,809
by 1.8 million in Hebei province.

83
00:03:07,809 --> 00:03:10,269
They don’t care how officials in Hebei do
it,

84
00:03:10,269 --> 00:03:12,749
as long as it gets done.

85
00:03:12,749 --> 00:03:13,879
And since whether you meet

86
00:03:13,879 --> 00:03:15,569
the central government’s goals

87
00:03:15,569 --> 00:03:18,950
is tied closely to whether you get promoted,

88
00:03:18,950 --> 00:03:22,049
local officials are motivated to do anything
they can

89
00:03:22,049 --> 00:03:24,000
to meet the numbers.

90
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,600
As one official put it,

91
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:27,760
local officials also don’t want to get blamed

92
00:03:27,769 --> 00:03:29,880
for not meeting the target.

93
00:03:29,880 --> 00:03:32,739
Yes, fear is a powerful motivator.

94
00:03:32,739 --> 00:03:36,239
And sometimes officials get too motivated.

95
00:03:36,239 --> 00:03:37,250
Like in Hebei,

96
00:03:37,250 --> 00:03:39,069
where they decided to reduce the number of

97
00:03:39,069 --> 00:03:42,329
coal-burning households by 2.3 million

98
00:03:42,329 --> 00:03:44,290
instead of 1.8 million.

99
00:03:44,290 --> 00:03:46,249
Exceeding expectations!

100
00:03:46,249 --> 00:03:48,249
By leaving people with no heat

101
00:03:48,249 --> 00:03:51,059
and triggering a natural gas shortage.

102
00:03:51,059 --> 00:03:52,909
The worst part, though,

103
00:03:52,909 --> 00:03:56,569
